{"title_page": "James Williams (labor leader)", "text_new": "{{other people|James Williams}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name   = James A. Williams\n| image     = James Williams IUPAT.jpg\n| caption  = Williams at a rally for Obama in 2008\n| birth_date  =\n| birth_place =\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| occupation  = President of [[International Union of Painters and Allied Trades|IUPAT]]\n| spouse      = Gerrie\n| children    =4 children\n}}\n'''James A. Williams''' is an American labor leader and President of the [[International Union of Painters and Allied Trades]] (IUP).<ref name=bio>{{cite web|title=JAMES A. WILLIAMS - General President |work=IUPAT About US |publisher=IUPAT |date= |url=http://www.iupat.org/about/bios/williams.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080907210751/http://www.iupat.org/about/bios/williams.html |archivedate=2008-09-07 |df= }}</ref> Williams is also the current Chairman of [[American Income Life Insurance Company]]'s Labor Advisory Board.<ref>{{cite web|title=Labor Advisory Board|url=http://www.ailife.com/main/company.aspx?submenu=Partners|publisher=American Income Life Insurance Company|accessdate=12 July 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712033342/http://www.ailife.com/main/company.aspx?submenu=Partners|archivedate=12 July 2011|df=}}</ref>\n\nHe graduated from [[Northeast Catholic High School]] in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]] in 1968. He served in the [[United States Army]] from 1969\u20131971 in the [[Vietnam War]], where he was awarded two Bronze Stars, the Army Accommodation Medal, and an Air Medal.<ref name=bio /> Upon his return home, he became a \"journeyman glazier.\"<ref name=bio />\n\n==References==\n{{commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williams, James}}\n[[Category:Activists from Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Leaders of American trade unions]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{worker-activist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{other people|James Williams}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name   = James A. Williams\n| image     = James Williams IUPAT.jpg\n| caption  = Williams at a rally for Obama in 2008\n| birth_date  =\n| birth_place =\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| occupation  = President of [[International Union of Painters and Allied Trades|IUPAT]]\n| spouse      = Gerrie\n| children    =4 children\n}}\n'''James A. Williams''' is an American labor leader and President of the [[International Union of Painters and Allied Trades]] (IUP).<ref name=bio>{{cite web|title=JAMES A. WILLIAMS - General President |work=IUPAT About US |publisher=IUPAT |date= |url=http://www.iupat.org/about/bios/williams.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080907210751/http://www.iupat.org/about/bios/williams.html |archivedate=2008-09-07 |df= }}</ref> Williams is also the current Chairman of [[American Income Life Insurance Company]]'s Labor Advisory Board.<ref>{{cite web|title=Labor Advisory Board|url=http://www.ailife.com/main/company.aspx?submenu=Partners|publisher=American Income Life Insurance Company|accessdate=12 July 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712033342/http://www.ailife.com/main/company.aspx?submenu=Partners|archivedate=12 July 2011|df=}}</ref>\n\nHe graduated from [[Northeast Catholic High School]] in [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]] in 1968. He served in the [[United States Army]] from 1969-1971 in the [[Vietnam War]], where he was awarded two Bronze Stars, the Army Accommodation Medal, and an Air Medal.<ref name=bio /> Upon his return home, he became a \"journeyman glazier.\"<ref name=bio />\n\n==References==\n{{commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Williams, James}}\n[[Category:Activists from Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Leaders of American trade unions]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{worker-activist-stub}}\n",